From 08a54819670aa46874afdd38c302a01bdb1b2b07 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kvds <kvds@example.invalid>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 06:39:48 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] mm: add experimental memory intent debugfs registry

Add an RFC v0, debugfs-only memory-intent registry targeted and validated
initially against Linux 6.8.12.

This patch is observability-only. It does not change reclaim behavior,
does not alter VM policy, and does not claim a stable ABI. The goal is to
let userspace register virtual-address ranges with generic intent flags so
research tooling can inspect what was tagged before any policy work is
attempted.

The interface is intentionally debugfs-only:

  /sys/kernel/debug/mm_intent/register
  /sys/kernel/debug/mm_intent/dump
  /sys/kernel/debug/mm_intent/clear

Input format for register is:

  <pid> <start_vaddr_hex> <length_hex> <intent_flags_hex> <deadline_ns> <priority>

Virtual-address ranges are used instead of PFNs because userspace naturally
knows virtual addresses, while PFNs are unstable under migration and often
hard to obtain.

This patch was compile-tested on Linux 6.8.12 and smoke-tested in QEMU
with a successful debugfs register and dump cycle.

---
 include/linux/memory_intent.h |  37 +++++++
 mm/Kconfig                    |  14 +++
 mm/Makefile                   |   1 +
 mm/memory_intent.c            | 197 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 4 files changed, 249 insertions(+)
